tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE population_demographics (
  location_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  city VARCHAR(255),
  state VARCHAR(255),
  population INT,
  area FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE population_demographics (
    city_name VARCHAR(50),
    population INT,
    median_age INT,
    median_income INT,
    land_area_sq_miles FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE land_use (
    city_name VARCHAR(50),
    residential_area_sq_miles FLOAT,
    commercial_area_sq_miles FLOAT,
    industrial_area_sq_miles FLOAT,
    agricultural_area_sq_miles FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE demographic_information (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  city VARCHAR,
  population INT,
  density FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE land_use (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  area FLOAT,
  land_type VARCHAR
)

CREATE TABLE population_density (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  city_id INT,
  density FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE land_planning (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  city_id INT,
  land_type VARCHAR,
  land_use_category VARCHAR
)

CREATE TABLE demographic_information (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR,
    ethnicity VARCHAR,
    population_density FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE land_use (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    land_type VARCHAR,
    zoning VARCHAR,
    area FLOAT,
    population INT
)

CREATE TABLE city (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    city_name VARCHAR,
    state VARCHAR,
    country VARCHAR,
    population INT
)

CREATE TABLE region (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    region_name VARCHAR,
    region_code INT,
    area FLOAT,
    population_density FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE demographic_trends (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    year INT,
    trend_type VARCHAR,
    trend_description VARCHAR,
    population_change INT
)
